<xsd:schema
	xmlns="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v3/services/getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredData"
	targetNamespace="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v3/services/getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredData"
	xmlns:epcore="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v2/components/core"
	xmlns:epbb="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v3/components/bankBase"
	xmlns:eppo="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v1/components/payoutBase"
	xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"
	elementFormDefault="qualified" >

   	<xsd:import namespace="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v3/components/bankBase" 
   		schemaLocation="../components/bankBaseTypes-3.0.xsd" />
    <xsd:import namespace="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v2/components/core" 
    	schemaLocation="../components/coreTypes-2.0.xsd" />
    <xsd:import namespace="http://customer.endpoint.earthport.com/api/merchant/v1/components/payoutBase" 
    	schemaLocation="../components/payoutBaseTypes-1.2.xsd" />

	<xsd:annotation>
		<xsd:documentation>

			This service is used to obtain the list of beneficiary bank account data which is required for each country / currency combination.
			
			This service should normally be used just before making a service request to "addBeneficiaryBankAccount" or
			"validateBeneficiaryBankAccount" in order to determine the mandatory bank account fields that will be expected 
			to be populated and to ensure they are supplied. This allows a single dynamic page for Bank registration 
			in all countries to be created.
			
			Input parameters which are required by the "getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredData" service
			
			The "countryCode" - Mandatory - (Please refer to the "CountryCodeType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is the country code of the country in which the beneficiary bank account is held.
								
			The "currencyCode" - Mandatory - (Please refer to the "CurrencyCodeType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is the currency in which payments / collections will be paid / received from / into the account.
										
			The "locale Type" - Optional - (Please refer to the "LocaleType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is a code which is used to identify the local language in which the information is to be displayed. 
							If there are specific localisation requirements please contact your Earthport Account Manager.
												
			The "serviceLevel" - Optional - (Please refer to the "ServiceLevelType" element in the payoutBaseTypes.xsd file)
							This determines the level of service with which the payment will be processed. There are only two options 
							which are currently available.
									
		</xsd:documentation>
	</xsd:annotation>

	<xsd:element name="getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredData"
		type="GetBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDataType" />

	<xsd:complexType name="GetBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDataType">
	
	<xsd:annotation>
		<xsd:documentation>

			Input parameters which are required by the "getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredData" service:
			
			The "countryCode" - Mandatory - (Please refer to the "CountryCodeType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is the country code of the country in which the beneficiary bank account is held.
								
			The "currencyCode" - Mandatory - (Please refer to the "CurrencyCodeType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is the currency in which payments / collections will be paid / received from / into the account.
										
			The "locale Type" - Optional - (Please refer to the "LocaleType" element in the coreTypes.xsd file)
							This is a code which is used to identify the local language in which the information is to be displayed. 
							If there are specific localisation requirements please contact your Earthport Account Manager.
												
			The "serviceLevel" - Optional - (Please refer to the "ServiceLevelType" element in the payoutBaseTypes.xsd file)
							This determines the level of service with which the payment will be processed. There are only two options 
							which are currently available.
									
		</xsd:documentation>
	</xsd:annotation>
	
		<xsd:sequence>
			<xsd:element name="countryCode" type="epcore:CountryCodeType"
				minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" />
			<xsd:element name="currencyCode" type="epcore:CurrencyCodeType"
				minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" />
			<xsd:element name="locale" type="epcore:LocaleType"
				minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" />
			<xsd:element name="serviceLevel" type="eppo:ServiceLevelType"
				minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" />
		</xsd:sequence>
		<xsd:attribute name="version" type="xsd:decimal" use="required" />
	</xsd:complexType>
  	
  	<xsd:element name="getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDataResponse" type="GetBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDataResponseType" />
	
  	<xsd:complexType name="GetBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDataResponseType">
	
	<xsd:annotation>
		<xsd:documentation>
		
			Parameters which are returned by the "getBeneficiaryBankAccountRequiredDetails" service response:

				The "beneficiaryBankAccountFieldGroupsList" - (Please refer to the "BeneficiaryBankAccountGroupsListType" element of the 
				baseBankType.xsd file)
						This describes one logical grouping of bank account data, although this may contain several different 
						"BeneficiaryBankAccountFieldGroup" records.
						Each "BeneficiaryBankAccountFieldGroup" record would normally be displayed in the User Interface (UI) on a 
						separate horizontal row.
				
		</xsd:documentation>
	</xsd:annotation>
    	<xsd:sequence minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1">
      		<xsd:element name="beneficiaryBankAccountFieldGroupsList" type="epbb:BeneficiaryBankAccountGroupsListType" />
    	</xsd:sequence>	
  	</xsd:complexType>
	
</xsd:schema>